723363f-a.title: Manhattan: Spring Street - Mulberry Street
723363f-a.text:
46 to 34 Spring Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of
Mulberry Street, showing a frame house (No. 46) at the corner and the New
York Dispensary (No. 36-34, 2-story building left) east of same. On the
right appears Nos. 212 to 206 Mulberry Street, adjoining and south of the
corner.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The 5-story tenement shown to the left and bearing a flour corpunT's
advertisement is to be demolished. It bears No. 40-42 Spring Street and
is reported in a list of demolitions carried in the New York Sun of
May 6, 1938.

723364f-b.title: Manhattan: Spring Street - Mulberry Street
723364f-b.text:
(1)
Spring Street, at, adjoining and east of the S.E. corner of Mulbeyry
Street. Also shown is Mulberry Street, at, adjoining and south of the
S.E. corner of Spring Street. Building shown at the corner (No. 46
Spring Street) is a 4-story frame structure.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 134.
(2)
The same, at an earlier date.
July 18, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
No. 40-42 Spring Street, a 5-story tenement shown at the extreme left
is to be dsmolished; being reported in a list of demolitions in the New
York Sun of May 6, 1938.
